    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Model Risk Level 3 assessment. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged; the assessment team determined that the single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol is standard practice for this device type and that the shortfall does not invalidate the overall credibility conclusion given the strong output comparison results (all E/uval < 1.96). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
